## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="573eb-181">Ao substituir o <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHost.OnClosed%2A> método você deve verificar se a base. Método OnClosed é chamado, mesmo se ocorre uma exceção.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="573eb-181">When overriding the <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHost.OnClosed%2A> method you must ensure the base.OnClosed method is called, even if an exception occurs.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="573eb-182">O código a seguir ilustra como fazer isso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="573eb-182">The following code illustrates how to do this.</span></span>  
  
```  
protected override void OnClosed()  
{  
    try  
    {  
        if (FaultFlagService.faultFlag == ThrowDuring.OnClosed)  
        {  
            FaultFlagService.faultFlag = ThrowDuring.Never;  
            throw new ServiceActivationException("Faulting the service because FaultFlagService.faultFlag = ThrowDuring.OnClosed");  
        }  
    }  
    finally  
    {  
        base.OnClosed();  
    }  
}  
  
```
